<lb corresp="#a1"/><w>sne</w><w>wrask<supplied>e</supplied></w><w>tāki<supplied>ñc</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><w>tar</w><w>ārśi-ype</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<w><supplied>tsälpi</supplied><lb corresp="#a3"/>ñc</w><w>klopäntwäṣ</w><pc>•</pc><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a4"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><w>r<supplied>it</supplied>wos</w><pc>:</pc><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>e</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<w><supplied>pākra</supplied><lb corresp="#a5"/>śik</w><w>y<supplied>pa</supplied>mträ</w><w>puk</w><w>n<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>a</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a6"/><w>mār</w><w>pu<supplied>t</supplied>t<supplied>i</supplied>śp<supplied>a</supplied>rn<supplied>a</supplied>c</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a7"/><w>ṣko</w><w>ṣpi</w><w>śke</w><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>ā</w><w>r</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<w><supplied>äṃ</supplied><lb corresp="#a8"/>tāne</w><w>saṃsā<supplied>r</supplied></w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="5"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><w>koc</w><w>kanweṃ</w><w>yāmu</w><pc>•</pc><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... may they be without illness!</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the land of Ārśi ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (may) they (be freed) from the sorrows! ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... is attached to ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... we make manifest ... All ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... I ... towards the Buddha worth ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... where the <hi>saṃsāra</hi> ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having lifted up [his] knees.</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">Part of the left side of a leaf: upper, lower and left margins (but not the string hole space) are preserved. This was apparently the last leaf of the manuscript, since the verso has only two lines while the remaining space is left blank. Of the leaf number can be read 〈[100]〉 〈60〉 〈8〉, but a digit above the 〈[100]〉 may have been lost. Both recto and verso are quite abraded.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment"><hi>tāki(ñc)</hi>: <hi>tāki(m)</hi>, <hi>tāki(ṣ)</hi> and <hi>tāki(mäs)</hi> are palaeographically impossible; <hi>tāki(ñc)</hi> is therefore the most likely.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">: cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegetal1931"/><citedRange>241</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/><citedRange>49a</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment"><hi>(pākra)śik</hi>: among the very few words ending in single <hi>śi</hi> (cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:poucha1955"/><citedRange>421</citedRange></bibl>), <hi>pākraśi</hi> is the only likely option here. The final <hi>-k</hi> is the emphatic particle.</note></p>
         </div>
